Description: Plate I, illustration to an unidentified work; five antiquarian objects marked "fig. 1 to fig. 4."; in top row on left a ram, and on right two sides of a coin, with recto lettered "ZEVC KACIOC"; in bottom row on left a figure of an Egyptian man in profile to right, and on right an Egyptian mummy case with hieroglyphs; border of single line on top and left, and double line on bottom and right. Etching and engraving
Curator's comments: One of two plates of similar formats, probably intended for the same publication - also see 1850,0223.625
Bibliographic references: Alexander 2008 / George Vertue as an Engraver (1045)
